          {
            "type": "TextTitle",
            "text": "Pronunciation tip"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Rate of speech"
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "text": [
              "Rate of speech refers to how fast or slow someone talks.",
              "If we speak too fast, it can be hard for people to understand us.",
              "If we speak too slowly, people might get bored or lose interest.",
              "As a speaker, it's important to vary the speed of your speech to keep your audience engaged.",
              "The best rate of speech depends on the situation and audience, but speaking at a pace of around 120-150 words per minute is generally considered effective for informal  situations.",
              "However, a pace of 60 to 75 words is considered effective in formal situations like presentations, meetings and video or audio calls."
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "ActionButtons",
            "text": {
              "event": "NextPage"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "SubPage",
        "text": [
          {
            "type": "TextTitle",
            "text": "Pronunciation tip"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Let’s see some guidelines to speeding and slowing down "
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Finding the right rate of speech, depending on the situations you are in can help ensure clear and effective communication."
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "text": [
              "Aim for a conversational pace, where you use a mix of fast and slow speeds.",
              "You can speak quickly to show excitement, urgency, or strong emotions, and speak slowly to emphasise important points or help the audience understand new ideas."
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "TextTitle",
            "text": "For example,"
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "text": [
              "A news anchor speaking at a moderate pace so that viewers can understand the information being shared easily.",
              "A stand-up comedian speaking quickly to keep the audience entertained and engaged.",
              "Your professor speaks slowly during a lecture to help students understand complex concepts.",
              "A motivational speaker using changes in pace to keep the audience interested and excited.",
              "A customer service representative speaks slowly and clearly to ensure that customers can follow instructions and get the help they need."
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "ActionButtons",
            "text": {
              "event": "NextPage"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
